| — | — | — | — | — | — | — | — |

## How to read this

- **Branch (from `dev`)**: the working branch the fix was committed on before the push to `dev`. Not a separate branch off `main`.
- **Verification**: how the fix was checked post-push (smoke test on dev, prod log delta, etc.).
- **Follow-up PR**: link to the PR that ports the same change through the normal `/run-issue` flow back into `dev`, so the audit trail isn't only here.

## Rules

- Hotfixes are for **production-impacting incidents only**. If the fix can wait for the next normal PR, it should.
- Hotfixes push to `dev`, never `main`. Merge `dev` → `main` happens through the usual release path.
- Every hotfix entry must reach a `Verification` value within 24 hours, or the hotfix command will refuse to run again until you fill it in.
